  "text": "Cell culture-adapted RV strains grown in MA-104 cells were used as control strains for G-and P-genotyping assays. G/P type designations are as recommended by the Rotavirus Classification Working Group [CITATION_1] and Reoviridae Study Group of the International Committee on Taxonomy of Viruses. The study was cleared by the IVIC ethic committee. A written informed consent was obtained from the parents or legal guardians at enrollment.",
